	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Memblers is right. Some games need both CIC trickery <em>and</em> a 50/60 switch. Either they explicitly check for frame length or they use raster effects that fall out of sync on the wrong TV system.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


