	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Actually, games just read a register that will tell them if the PPU is running in NTSC or PAL mode. You don't need anything fancy to detect the video mode on SNES. Assuming a game doesn't do that then all that is stopping it from running is the CIC. Though SDD1 and SA-1 custom chips actually do their own region checking/lockout.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


